The plan, he and other Utah leaders explained, is more akin to a light dial than a light switch.
The updated state plan comes after President Donald Trump gave governors a three-phase plan to reopen the national economy.
Spencer Cox, who oversees the state's coronavirus task force, insisted that Utah's plan was drafted with state health department officials included in meetings.
After the press conference, state health officials issued a statement in support of the plan.
